/*
The idea is the same as in https://www.shadertoy.com/view/sl3BWs
The difference is that now the intersection of both
green circles with the cubic bezier curve is computed.

In the quadratic bezier case, one always has an
intersection with the green circle where the incenter lies on.

In the cubic bezier case, one has to check both green circles
for intersections.

Also, the polynomial equation one has to solve is quartic
instead of quadratic now, so this is much more involved computationally.

There should always be exactly one intersection.
(I've read this somewhere, not sure how to prove this)
*/

//#define MOVE_NODE /* Move the node with the mouse instead */

const vec3 dot_col=vec3(0);
const vec3 line_col=vec3(0);
